nodes.name: Definition of scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s) (if (scale s) (and (compositeEntity s) (exists (s1 e x y s2 s3) (and (componentsOf s1 s) (partialOrdering e x y s) (subset s2 s3)(relationsOf s3 s) (forall (e1) (if (member e1 s2) (exists (x1 y1) (and (member x1 s1)(member y1 s1) (subst2 x1 y1 e1 x y e)))))))))))
nodes.english: A scale is a composite entity with components and a partial ordering relation among them

nodes.name: Partial ordering constraints
nodes.fol: (forall (e x y s) (if (partialOrdering e x y s) (and (scale s)(arg* x e)(arg* y e))))
nodes.english: If e is a partial ordering on scale s, then s is a scale and e is a relation between x and y

nodes.name: Definition of inScale
nodes.fol: (forall (y s) (iff (inScale y s) (and (scale s)(componentOf y s))))
nodes.english: Being in a scale is an abbreviation for being a component of a scale

nodes.name: Definition of lts (less than scale)
nodes.fol: (forall (e x1 y1 s) (iff (lts' e1 x1 y1 s) (exists (e x y e1) (and (partialOrdering e x y s) (subst2 x y e x1 y1 e1)))))
nodes.english: lts defines a 'less than' relation relative to a particular scale s using substitution into the partial ordering

nodes.name: Partial ordering is antireflexive
nodes.fol: (forall (x s) (not (lts x x s)))
nodes.english: The partial ordering is antireflexive - no element is less than itself

nodes.name: Partial ordering is antisymmetric
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (if (lts x y s)(not (lts y x s))))
nodes.english: The partial ordering is antisymmetric - if x < y then not y < x

nodes.name: Partial ordering is transitive
nodes.fol: (forall (x y z s) (if (and (lts x y s)(lts y z s)) (lts x z s)))
nodes.english: The partial ordering is transitive - if x < y and y < z then x < z

nodes.name: Definition of gts (greater than scale)
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (iff (gts y x s)(lts x y s)))
nodes.english: Greater than is defined as the reverse of less than

nodes.name: lts argument constraints
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (if (lts x y s) (and (or (inScale x s) (exists (x1) (and (at x x1 s)(inScale x1 s)))) (or (inScale y s) (exists (y1) (and (at y y1 s)(inScale y1 s)))))))
nodes.english: Arguments of lts must be either points on the scale or entities at points on the scale

nodes.name: at relation preserves ordering
nodes.fol: (forall (x1 x2 y1 y2 s) (and (if (at x1 y1 s) (iff (lts x1 y2 s)(lts y1 y2 s))) (if (at x2 y2 s) (iff (lts y1 x2 s)(lts y1 y2 s))) (if (and (at x1 y1 s)(at x2 y2 s)) (iff (lts x1 x2 s)(lts y1 y2 s)))))
nodes.english: The at relation preserves the partial ordering - entities at points inherit the ordering of those points

nodes.name: Definition of onScale
nodes.fol: (forall (x s) (iff (onScale x s) (or (inScale x s) (exists (y) (and (inScale y s)(at x y s))))))
nodes.english: onScale covers both points in a scale and entities at points in a scale

nodes.name: Definition of leqs (less than or equal scale)
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (iff (leqs x y s) (or (lts x y s) (and (onScale x s)(equal x y)))))
nodes.english: Less than or equal is either less than or equal (for entities on the scale)

nodes.name: Definition of geqs (greater than or equal scale)
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (iff (geqs x y s) (or (gts x y s) (and (onScale x s)(equal x y)))))
nodes.english: Greater than or equal is either greater than or equal (for entities on the scale)

nodes.name: Antisymmetric property for leqs
nodes.fol: (forall (x y s) (if (and (leqs x y s)(leqs y x s)) (equal x y)))
nodes.english: If x ≤ y and y ≤ x, then x = y (antisymmetry for ≤)

nodes.name: Definition of top of scale
nodes.fol: (forall (x s) (iff (top x s) (and (inScale x s) (forall (y) (if (inScale y s)(leqs y x s))))))
nodes.english: The top of a scale is the highest point - all other points are less than or equal to it

nodes.name: Definition of bottom of scale
nodes.fol: (forall (x s) (iff (bottom x s) (and (inScale x s) (forall (y) (if (inScale y s)(leqs x y s))))))
nodes.english: The bottom of a scale is the lowest point - it is less than or equal to all other points

nodes.name: Definition of subscale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (iff (subscale s1 s) (and (scale s1)(scale s) (forall (x) (if (inScale x s1)(inScale x s))) (forall (x y) (iff (lts x y s1) (and (inScale x s1)(inScale y s1) (lts x y s)))))))
nodes.english: A subscale has a subset of components and the partial ordering restricted to that subset

nodes.name: Definition of reverse scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (iff (reverse s1 s) (and (scale s1)(scale s) (forall (x y) (and (iff (inScale x s)(inScale x s1)) (iff (lts x y s)(lts y x s1)))))))
nodes.english: The reverse of a scale has the same components but reversed partial ordering

nodes.name: Disjoint scales
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s2) (if (and (scale s1)(scale s2)) (iff (disjoint s1 s2) (exists (s3 s4) (and (componentsOf s3 s1)(componentsOf s4 s2) (disjoint s3 s4))))))
nodes.english: Two scales are disjoint if their sets of components are disjoint

nodes.name: Definition of total ordering
nodes.fol: (forall (e x y s) (if (lts' e x y s) (iff (totalOrdering e x y s) (forall (x1 y1) (if (and (inScale x1 s)(inScale y1 s)) (or (lts x1 y1 s)(equal x1 y1) (lts y1 x1 s)))))))
nodes.english: A total ordering is a partial ordering where any two elements are comparable

nodes.name: Scales are grounds
nodes.fol: (forall (s) (if (scale s)(ground s)))
nodes.english: A scale is potentially a ground - entities can be located 'at' points on a scale

nodes.name: Extended function definition for scales
nodes.fol: (forall (f s1 s2) (iff (function f s1 s2) (exists (s3 s4) (and (if (set s1)(equal s3 s1)) (if (scale s1)(componentsOf s3 s1)) (if (set s2)(equal s4 s2)) (if (scale s2)(componentsOf s4 s2)) (function0 f s3 s4)))))
nodes.english: Extends the notion of function to scales by using their component sets as domain/range

nodes.name: Definition of monotone increasing function
nodes.fol: (forall (f s1 s2) (if (and (function f s1 s2)(scale s1)(scale s2)) (iff (monotoneIncreasing f) (forall (x1 x2 y1 y2) (if (and (map f x1 y1)(map f x2 y2)(lts x1 x2 s1)) (lts y1 y2 s2))))))
nodes.english: A scale-to-scale function is monotone-increasing if it preserves the 'less than' ordering

nodes.name: Definition of function into
nodes.fol: (forall (f s1 s3) (iff (functionInto f s1 s3) (exists (s2) (and (or (subset s2 s3)(subscale s2 s3)) (function f s1 s2)))))
nodes.english: A function f is 'into' a set or scale s3 if there is a subset or subscale s2 for which f is onto

nodes.name: Definition of scaleDefinedBy
nodes.fol: (forall (s s1 e) (iff (scaleDefinedBy s s1 e) (and (scale s)(componentsOf s1 s) (exists (x y) (partialOrdering e x y s)))))
nodes.english: A scale is defined by specifying the set of entities as components and the relation as partial ordering

nodes.name: Sequence as scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s s1 e x y) (if (and (sequence s)(componentsOf s1 s) (beforeInSeq' e x y s)) (and (scaleDefinedBy s s1 e) (forall (z)(if (first z s)(bottom z s))))))
nodes.english: A sequence is a scale whose partial ordering is the beforeInSeq relation, with first element as bottom

nodes.name: Set of sets as scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 e x y) (if (and (forall (s2)(if (member s2 s1)(set s2))) (subset' e x y)) (exists (s) (and (scaleDefinedBy s s1 e) (forall (z) (if (and (member z s1)(null z)) (bottom z s)))))))
nodes.english: A set of sets under the subset relation is a scale, with null set as bottom if present

nodes.name: Definition of subset consistent scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s e) (iff (subsetConsistent s e) (and (scale s)(eventuality e) (forall (s0)(if (argn s0 1 e)(set s0))) (forall (x)(if (argn x 2 e)(exists (y)(at x y s)))) (forall (e1 e2 s1 s2 x1 x2) (if (and (instance e1 e)(argn s1 1 e1) (argn x1 2 e1) (instance e2 e)(argn s2 1 e2) (argn x2 2 e2) (subset s1 s2)) (leqs x1 x2 s))))))
nodes.english: A scale whose ordering is consistent with the subset ordering among sets associated with entities placed at points in the scale

nodes.name: Monotonicity condition for subset mapping
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s2 x1 x2 s) (if (and (subset s1 s2)(r s1 x1)(r s2 x2)) (leqs x1 x2 s)))
nodes.english: Given some mapping r, if s1 ⊆ s2 and r maps s1 to x1 and s2 to x2, then x1 ≤ x2 on the scale

nodes.name: Definition of composite scale
nodes.fol: (forall (s s1 s2) (if (compositeScale s s1 s2) (and (exists (s3) (and (componentsOf s3 s1)(componentsOf s3 s2) (componentsOf s3 s))) (forall (x y) (if (and (lts x y s1)(leqs x y s2)) (lts x y s))) (forall (x y) (if (and (leqs x y s1)(lts x y s2)) (lts x y s))))))
nodes.english: A composite scale has the same components as two original scales and ordering consistent with both

nodes.name: Hi region is subscale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (if (Hi s1 s)(subscale s1 s)))
nodes.english: The Hi region of a scale is a subscale

nodes.name: Md region is subscale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (if (Md s1 s)(subscale s1 s)))
nodes.english: The Md (middle) region of a scale is a subscale

nodes.name: Lo region is subscale
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (if (Lo s1 s)(subscale s1 s)))
nodes.english: The Lo (low) region of a scale is a subscale

nodes.name: Top of scale is top of Hi region
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (if (Hi s1 s) (forall (x) (iff (top x s)(top x s1)))))
nodes.english: The top of the scale is in the Hi region and is the top of the Hi region

nodes.name: Bottom of scale is bottom of Lo region
nodes.fol: (forall (s1 s) (if (Lo s1 s) (forall (x) (iff (bottom x s)(bottom x s1)))))
nodes.english: The bottom of a scale is the bottom of its Lo region

nodes.name: Lo region is less than Hi region
nodes.fol: (forall (s s1 s2 x y) (if (and (Hi s1 s)(Lo s2 s)(inScale x s1)(inScale y s2)) (lts y x s)))
nodes.english: If a point is in the Lo region, then it is less than all the points in the Hi region

nodes.name: Definition of scaleFor
nodes.fol: (forall (s e) (iff (scaleFor s e) (exists (s1) (and (Hi s1 s) (forall (e1 x y) (if (and (at' e1 x y s1)(argn x 1 e)) (iff (Rexist e)(Rexist e1))))))))
nodes.english: An entity x has property e exactly when x is at a point in the Hi region of scale s - connects absolute adjectives to their underlying scales

nodes.name: Hi region properties are goal-relevant
nodes.fol: (forall (e x y s1 s) (if (and (at' e x y s1)(Hi s1 s)(etc)) (exists (c a g g1) (and (member e c)(goal g a) (or (causalComplex c g) (and (not' g1 g)(causalComplex c g1)))))))
nodes.english: If something is in the Hi region of a scale, then defeasibly that property plays a causal role in some agent's goal being achieved or not achieved

node_types.variable: Frequently used variables (2+ axioms in chapter)
